OL,3,CSon of Aubrey Hames says his father
OL,4,Cnever got over wrongful corruption
OL,5,Cclaims
OL,7,FThe son of one of Wales' best-known
OL,8,Flocal councillors in the 1970s and
OL,9,F'80s says his father never got over
OL,10,Fbeing wrongly accused of corruption.
OL,12,FAubrey Hames won a record compensation
OL,13,Fpayout and an apology from a former
OL,14,Fprime minister after the charges
OL,15,Fagainst him were thrown out in 1979.
OL,17,FBut he never worked again, although he
OL,18,Fcontinued to serve as a councillor
OL,19,Funtil retiring from politics in 1987.
