OL,4,Cnever got over wrongful corruption
OL,5,Cclaims
OL,7,FAubrey Hames was accused of granting
OL,8,Fcontracts favouring the haulage firm
OL,9,Fof Lihu Ichilov and taking a family
OL,10,Fholiday to Israel, paid for by Mr
OL,11,FIchilov, despite having proof that he,
OL,12,FMr Hames, had paid for it himself.
OL,14,FThe cases against both were thrown out
OL,15,Fin 1979 but Aubrey Hames never worked
OL,16,Fagain, winning an unfair dismissal
OL,17,Fclaim which led to a then record
OL,18,F#11,635 compensation payout.
