OL,5,Cclaims
OL,7,FAn independent review in 1985 found
OL,8,Fthat the investigation was
OL,9,F"incompetently authorised" and
OL,10,F"incompetently conducted".
OL,12,FAubrey Hames spent nearly a decade
OL,13,Ftrying to clear his name but was
OL,14,Ffrustrated by bureaucracy and an
OL,15,Funwillingness to reopen the case. He
OL,16,Fbecame convinced that corruption
OL,17,Fwithin the British Transport Police at
OL,18,Fthe time, combined with a
OL,19,Fdetermination to prosecute local
OL,20,Fpoliticians, had led to his downfall.
