OL,4,Cnever got over wrongful corruption
OL,5,Cclaims
OL,7,FAnd he says his father's efforts to
OL,8,Fget answers at the highest level were
OL,9,Fbecause "he was wronged" and that
OL,10,F"even though he had been cleared and
OL,11,Fthe case had been thrown out there was
OL,12,Fstill that belief that if you get
OL,13,Faccused of something, that you are
OL,14,Fguilty.
OL,16,F"Even now, when I wished him a happy
OL,17,Fhundredth birthday on Facebook last
OL,18,Fyear, somebody put a post saying he
OL,19,Fwas 'charged with fiddling'.
